{
  "id": "fenicsx-poisson-2d-basic",
  "name": "2D Poisson Equation - Basic",
  "simulator": "fenicsx",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Solves the 2D Poisson equation -∇²u = f on a unit square [0,1] × [0,1] with homogeneous Dirichlet boundary conditions (u = 0 on ∂Ω). The source term is a Gaussian centered at (0.5, 0.5): f = 10*exp(-((x-0.5)² + (y-0.5)²)/0.02). This is a fundamental benchmark for testing FEniCSx finite element capabilities.",
  "category": "finite-element",
  "difficulty": "beginner",
  "tags": ["poisson", "elliptic-pde", "2d", "dirichlet", "linear"],
